revision.text:
{{One source|date=June 2016}}
'''93.3 Central FM''' (93.3 [[FM broadcasting|FM]]) was a non-profit community [[radio station]] based on the island of [[Malta]] and serving mainly [[three villages of Malta]]: [[Attard]], [[Lija]] and [[Balzan]]. 93.3 Central FM went on air on {{cn-span|15 January 2006|reason=The ref to the Malta Times already mentioned the station in 2004|date=June 2016}}.

==Overview==
The station was founded and managed by Maltese radio personality [[Andre` Bugeja]] and [[Clayton Camilleri]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20040805/local/new-community-radio.115976 |title=New community radio |newspaper=Times of Malta |date=5 August 2004}}</ref> Located in Attard, a central and densely populated location on the island of Malta, Central FM managed to reach a wide audience thanks to its ongoing, community centric and entertaining programming. The station transmitted on 93.3&nbsp;MHz from the center of Malta and all around the world on the World Wide Web.

The station motto was 'Transmitting from the center of the island' ("{{lang|mt|L-istazzjon li jxandar mic-centru ta' Malta}}").

93.3 Central FM also trained various young aspiring radio presenters who have today managed to follow a professional media career. The station was the first ever [[community radio]] station on the Maltese islands to broadcast using high radio standards. CentralFM was also famous amongst the English-speaking community as it collaborated with a number of foreign radio personalities stationed in America, UK, and Australia .

Central FM terminated its broadcast due to personal commitments from the management who stated they would be working on new projects in the future.

