{{Infobox mine | name = Gremnik | image = | width = | caption = | pushpin_map = | pushpin_label = | pushpin_map_caption = | coordinates = | place = [[Klina]] | subdivision_type = [[Municipalities of Kosova|Municipality]] | state/province = [[District of Peja]] | country = [[Kosovo]] | owner = [[Boxitet e Kosovës]] | stock_exchange = None | stock_code = [[Government-owned corporation|State owned]] | official website = | acquisition year = | products = [[Bauxite]] | financial year = | amount = | opening year = | closing year = }} The Gremnik is one of the largest [[bauxite]] mines in [[Kosovo]].<ref name="Kiruna">{{cite web|url=http://www.beak.de/pdf/news/KosovoMiningJournal.pdf |title=Kosovo Mining Journal |year=2010 |publisher=beak.de |accessdate=2010-10-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718201825/http://www.beak.de/pdf/news/KosovoMiningJournal.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-18 |df= }}</ref> The mine is located in [[Klina]] in [[District of Peć]].<ref name="Kiruna" /> The mine has reserves amounting to 3.66 million tonnes of ore grading 40.49% [[bauxite]].<ref name="Kiruna"/>
