{{Infobox Journal | title = Journal of African Cultural Studies | cover = Journal of African Cultural Studies cover.gif | discipline = [[African studies]] | formernames = African Languages and Cultures | abbreviation = J. Afr. Cult. Stud. | publisher = [[Routledge]] | country = | history = 1988-present | frequency = Biannually | website = http://www.tandfonline.com/action/aboutThisJournal?journalCode=cjac20 | link1 = http://www.tandfonline.com/toc/cjac20/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://www.tandfonline.com/loi/cjac20 | link2-name = Online archive | ISSN = 1469-9346 | eISSN = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 50709779 | LCCN = }} The '''''Journal of African Cultural Studies''''' is a biannual [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering research on [[African culture]], including [[African literature]]s, both written and oral, [[performance art]]s, [[visual art]]s, [[music]], the role of the media, the relationship between culture and power, culture and gender issues and sociolinguistic topics of cultural interest. It was established in 1988 as ''African Languages and Culture'' and obtained its current title in 1998.
== History == This journal continues ''African Language Studies''. There was a 10-year hiatus between the publications.<ref>Editorial. 1988. African Languages and Cultures 1.1:2 DOI:10.1080/09544168808717675</ref>
