{{Infobox film | name = Les Écuelles | image = | caption = | director = [[Idrissa Ouedraogo]] | producer = Les Films de l'Avenir | writer = | starring = | distributor = | released = {{film date|1983}} | runtime = 11 minutes | country = Burkina Faso | language = | budget = | gross = | screenplay = Idrissa Ouedraogo | cinematography = Issaka Thiombiano | sound = Arsène Ilboudo | editing = Arnaud Blin | music = }}
'''''Les Écuelles ''''' is a 1983 [[Culture of Burkina Faso|Burkinabé]] film.
== Synopsis == This short film takes place in northern [[Burkina Faso]], in a [[Mossi people|Mossi]] village. There, two old men patiently and skillfully make traditional wooden bowls for everyday use. Meanwhile, the young people leave the village to go to the city and abandon these tricky crafts.
