[[File:N&SAmerica-pol.jpg|thumb|250px|Political map of the Americas]]
This is a '''list of active stock exchanges in the Americas'''. [[Stock exchange]]s in [[Latin America]] (where [[Spanish language|Spanish]] and [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] prevail) use the term ''Bolsa de Valores'', meaning "bag" or "purse of "values." (compare [[börse (disambiguation)|börse]] in [[German language|German]] or [[bourse (disambiguation)|bourse]] in [[French language|French]]).
The [[Caribbean]] has one major [[regional stock exchange]]: the [[Eastern Caribbean Securities Exchange]] (ECSE), which serves [[Anguilla]], [[Antigua and Barbuda]], [[Dominica]], [[Grenada]], [[Montserrat]], [[Saint Kitts and Nevis]], [[Saint Lucia]], and [[Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]]. The service area of the ECSE corresponds to the service area of the [[Eastern Caribbean Central Bank]], with which it is associated.
