{{Infobox song contest entry <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Eurovision Song Contest--> | song = {{flagicon|Lithuania}} "Love" | image = [[File:Sasha Son - Love.JPG|180px]] | caption = | year = 2009 | country = Lithuania | artist = [[Sasha Son]] | as = | with = | language = English | languages = | composer = [[Sasha Son]] | lyricist = [[Sasha Son]] | place = 23rd | points = 23 | place_semi = 9th | points_semi = 66 | prev = Nomads in the Night | prev_link = Nomads in the Night | next = Eastern European Funk | next_link = Eastern European Funk }} '''"Love"''', known by its [[Lithuanian language|Lithuanian]] name''' "Pasiklydęs žmogus"''' (''The Lost Man'') is a song by [[Lithuania]]n singer [[Sasha Son]], the Lithuanian entry to the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2009]], where it was performed in [[English language|English]] with the final verse in [[Russian language|Russian]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esctoday.com/news/read/13249|title=Lithuania has chosen for Eurovision 2009|last=Floras|first=Stella|date=2009-02-14|publisher=''ESCToday''|accessdate=2009-02-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oikotimes.com/v2/index.php?file=articles&id=5124|title=Sasha Son to Moscow!|last=Supranavicius|first=Alekas|date=2009-02-14|publisher=''Oikotimes''|accessdate=2009-02-14|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090218104009/http://oikotimes.com/v2/index.php?file=articles&id=5124|archivedate=2009-02-18|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurovision.tv/page/news?id=1923|title=Lithuanian trophy goes to Sasha Son|last=Siim|first=Jarmo|date=2009-02-14|publisher=''Eurovision.tv''|accessdate=2009-02-14}}</ref>
The song competed in the second semi-final on 14 May 2009 and qualified for the final, where it tied with the Spanish entry, coming in 23rd with 23 points.
