'''Rotana Masriya''' ({{lang-ar|روتانا مصرية}}) is a [[free-to-air]] [[satellite TV]] general entertainment unencrypted channel that is owned by [[Rotana Group]] network. It was launched on 21 May 2011, after the [[Egyptian uprising]] in January 2011. The channel won the award of The Best Youth Show in [[Arab World|the whole Arabic speaking world]] in the second year of Cairo's Radio and [[TV Mondial]].<ref>http://www.eventgate.net/?con=events&page=event&id=10935&title=The+Closing+Ceremony+of+the+Arab+Radio+and+Television+Mondial</ref><ref>http://www.kuna.net.kw/ArticleDetails.aspx?id=2351868&language=en</ref> The channel got a wide international coverage after featuring a birthday party which appeared like a marriage of two men in Egypt,<ref>http://www.ibtimes.com/egypt-imprisons-8-gay-wedding-video-case-1717360</ref> where same-sex relationships are not illegable, but are punishable.<ref>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/12/09/world/africa/egypts-gay-community-living-in-fear/</ref>

