[[File:Wahlkreis Uukwiyu in Oshana.png|right|thumb|Uukwiyu Constituency (yellow) in the Oshana Region (dark grey)]]

'''Uukwiyu Constituency''' is an [[Constituencies of Namibia|electoral constituency]] in the [[Oshana Region]] of [[Namibia]]. It has 11,894 inhabitants,<ref>[http://www.statoids.com/yna.html Constituencies of Namibia, 2004]</ref> its district capital is the settlement of [[Uukwiyu]].

==Politics==
Uukwiyu constituency is traditionally a stronghold of the [[South West Africa People's Organization]] (SWAPO) party. 

In the [[Namibian local and regional elections, 2010|2010 regional elections]], [[SWAPO]]'s [[Andreas N. Amundjindi]] won the constituency with 3,701 votes. His only challenger was Salmi Benjameni of the [[Rally for Democracy and Progress (Namibia)|Rally for Democracy and Progress]], who received 48 votes.<ref>[http://www.ecn.na/results/2010/Press_Release_Constituency_-_Oshana-Uukwiyu.pdf Results from the Electoral Commission of Namibia]</ref> In the [[Namibian local and regional elections, 2015|2015 local and regional elections]] the SWAPO candidate won uncontested and became councillor after no opposition party nominated a candidate.<ref name=uncontested>{{cite news|last=Kangootui |first=Nomhle |newspaper=[[The Namibian]] |title=Swapo gets ǃNamiǂNûs uncontested |url=http://www.namibian.com.na/index.php?page=read&id=33153 |date=23 October 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151024163513/http://www.namibian.com.na/index.php?page=read&id=33153 |archivedate=October 24, 2015 }}</ref>

